definition: to deliver/to carry/to give (as a present)/to present (with)/to see off/to send
to walk (side part of split character)
to send/to give as a present
to transmit/to dispatch/to issue (an official document or credential)
to put together an order and deliver it (i.e. 配貨|配货[pei4 huo4] and 送貨|送货[song4 huo4])/to deliver (goods)
picking up and dropping off/greeting and sending off/shuttle (transport service)
to see someone off/to throw someone a send-off party

sentences.english: That good for nothing never sends any money to his poor mother.
sentences.chinese: 那個沒用的傢伙，從不給他可憐的母親送錢。

sentences.english: I'll order a special messenger to deliver the document.
sentences.chinese: 我會派專人把文件送去。

sentences.english: Chandler wants Monica to wear the earings he gave her.
sentences.chinese: 錢德希望莫妮卡戴上他送的耳環。

sentences.english: I send one to you eat, I believe you will like.
sentences.chinese: 我送一個給你喫口巴，相信你一定會喜歡的。

sentences.english: I send this Valen tine’s card to remind you that I love you.
sentences.chinese: 我送上這張卡片，爲的是要提醒你，我愛你。

sentences.english: This little present is for you as a token of our love. We hope you can use it.
sentences.chinese: 送你這個小禮物，聊表我心意，希望你能用得上。

sentences.english: We are trying to help out by delivering flour to bakeries.
sentences.chinese: 我們正在設法給麪包店送去麪粉，幫助它們度過難關。

sentences.english: CBRC shall, on the same day as issuing the approval certificate, submit to the Ministry of Commerce the approval certificate stub.
sentences.chinese: 銀監會在代發當日將批准證書存根送商務部。

sentences.english: Police say Chin appeared fine when guards brought breakfast to his cell.
sentences.chinese: 警方稱陳在獄卒給他送早餐的時候看上去一切正常。

sentences.english: Her son was sent to the big house for stealing classified papers.
sentences.chinese: 她的兒子因爲盜竊歸好類的文件而被送進了監獄。

sentences.english: Left to right and so on and so on cock not send red crown to the centipede, they come in person to discuss.
sentences.chinese: 公雞左等右等不見蜈蚣送紅冠來，就親自上門討要。

sentences.english: I'd love to send a probe in there to find out what's really going on.
sentences.chinese: 我很想送一個探測器去那裏，看看到底發生了什麼。

sentences.english: Eg . If you go on ill-treating your wife like this , you will be taken to court .
sentences.chinese: 如果你再這樣對待你的妻子，你就會被送上法庭。

sentences.english: This torch is then carried by a relay of runners to the site of the Summer or Winter games.
sentences.chinese: 之後這支火炬由跑者接力送至夏季或冬季比賽地點。

sentences.english: The seed corn was given me.

definition: to send/to give as a present
to send to/to deliver to/to give sb a lift (e.g. in a car)
to give away/to accompany/to see sb off
to celebrate a birthday/to give a birthday party
to receive/to answer (the phone)/to meet or welcome sb/to connect/to catch/to join/to extend/to take one's turn on duty/to take over for sb
to bring sth to sb/to deliver
